saint /seɪnt/

(saints) 

1. N-COUNT/N-TITLE A saint is someone who has died and been officially recognized and honoured by the Christian church because his or her life was a perfect example of the way Christians should live. (基督教教会正式追封的) 圣人 

例： Every parish was named after a saint. 每个教区都以一个圣徒的名字命名。 

2. N-COUNT If you refer to a living person as a saint , you mean that they are extremely kind, patient, and unselfish. 圣人 [表赞许] 

例： My girlfriend Geraldine is a saint to put up with me. 我的女友杰拉尔丁是个能包容我的圣人。

</div>

